# Walkthrough - Final Stability & Crash Fixes

I have implemented a final set of critical fixes to ensure the game is stable and doesn't crash during gameplay or loading.

## Critical Fixes Implemented

### 1. Robust Navigation & Loading
- **[main.dart](file:///Users/amolsehgal/antigravity%20-%20touchline%20tantrum/touchline_tantrum/lib/main.dart)**: Added comprehensive error handling to the `/game` route. If saved data is corrupt or missing, it now safely redirects back to the setup screen instead of crashing.
- **[game_screen.dart](file:///Users/amolsehgal/antigravity%20-%20touchline%20tantrum/touchline_tantrum/lib/screens/game_screen.dart)**: Added safety checks (`if (!mounted) return;`) immediately after every asynchronous step in the game's initialization process.

### 2. Audio Stability
- **[audio_manager.dart](file:///Users/amolsehgal/antigravity%20-%20touchline%20tantrum/touchline_tantrum/lib/utils/audio_manager.dart)**: Switched from unstable 404 URLs to local asset placeholders (`audio/stadium_cheer.mp3`). This prevents native audio engine crashes that can occur when trying to stream dead links.
  > [!IMPORTANT]
  > Please ensure the MP3 files exist in `assets/audio/` for sound effects to play.

### 3. Ticker Performance
- **[breaking_news_ticker.dart](file:///Users/amolsehgal/antigravity%20-%20touchline%20tantrum/touchline_tantrum/lib/widgets/breaking_news_ticker.dart)**: Refactored the infinite scroll logic. It now uses a safer boundary check (`maxScrollExtent - 5`) to trigger the reset, avoiding potential race conditions or jitter when the ticker loops.

### 4. Layout Corrections
- **[manager_mood.dart](file:///Users/amolsehgal/antigravity%20-%20touchline%20tantrum/touchline_tantrum/lib/widgets/manager_mood.dart)**: Removed the internal `Positioned` widget.
- **[game_screen.dart](file:///Users/amolsehgal/antigravity%20-%20touchline%20tantrum/touchline_tantrum/lib/screens/game_screen.dart)**: Correctly applied `Positioned` within the parent `Stack`, fixing a Flutter layout error.

## Verification Results

- **Stability**: Tested navigation loops and rapid restarts; no more "setState() called after dispose()" or "Undefined Route" errors.
- **Analysis**: `flutter analyze` shows 0 errors and 0 warnings (excluding minor deprecations).
- **Performance**: The news ticker and game timers are now running efficiently without memory bloat.
